3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20are%20young%20people%20doing%20with%20their%20newfound%20cash%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20bucking%20the%20stereotype%20of%20freewheeling%20youth%20partying%20and%20squandering%20their%20funds.%20Many%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-quiet-quitting-work-ethic-millennials-money-struggles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewatched%20their%20parents%20and%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E%20weather%20previous%20recessions%20and%20learned%20how%20precarious%20the%20economy%20can%20be.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20taking%20a%20more%20cautious%20approach%20to%20their%20financial%20futures%20and%20using%20their%20paychecks%20to%20try%20to%20get%20a%20leg%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20May%20survey%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfainstitute.org%2Fabout%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2Ffinra-cfa-institute-gen-z-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECFA%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20global%20trade%20association%20for%20investment%20advisors%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20said%20they%20were%20already%20investing%2C%20and%2082%25%20of%20American%20Gen%20Z%20investors%20said%20they%20began%20investing%20before%20they%20turned%2021.%20That's%20significantly%20higher%20than%20the%2031%25%20of%20millennials%20and%2014%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20who%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finrafoundation.org%2Fsites%2Ffinrafoundation%2Ffiles%2FUncertain-Futures-Issue-Brief-7-Myths-about-Millennials-and-Investing_1_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2018%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20began%20investing%20at%20that%20age.%20Of%20the%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20are%20already%20in%20the%20market%2C%20just%20under%2090%25%20said%20they%20were%20actively%20making%20trades%20in%20response%20to%20economic%20factors%20such%20as%20inflation%20and%20rising%20interest%20rates%2C%20an%20April%20Bankrate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Finvesting%2Fsurvey-market-volatility-stocks-may-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%2C%20by%20far%20the%20highest%20of%20the%20generations.%20Overall%2C%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2023%2F10%2F18%2Fpercentage-americans-own-stock-market-investing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20stock%20in%202022%20than%20in%20any%20previous%20year%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20economic%20uncertainty%20that%20worries%20young%20people%20but%20also%20planning%20for%20retirement.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20those%20surveyed%20by%20the%20CFA%20Institute%20said%20they%20were%20investing%20to%20be%20able%20to%20retire%20when%20they%20wanted%20to.%20Given%20that%20financial%20advisors%20say%20that%20Gen%20Z%20will%20need%20roughly%20%243%20million%20for%20a%2020-year%20retirement%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high%20bar%20even%20for%20smart%20money%20managers%20%E2%80%94%20young%20people%20aren't%20wasting%20any%20time.%20Overall%2C%2066%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20surveyed%20by%20the%20Transamerica%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20Studies%20said%20they'd%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftransamericainstitute.org%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Fresearch%2Fpost-pandemic-retirement-realities-multigenerational-workforce-report-july-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaving%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stashing%20away%20a%20median%2020%25%20of%20their%20annual%20pay%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20double%20the%20share%20of%20income%20that%20older%20generations%20said%20they%20were%20stashing%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertain%20financial%20circumstances%20of%20the%20generation%20and%20growing%20access%20to%20financial%20products%20have%20inspired%20a%20willingness%20among%20Gen%20Z%20to%20jump%20headfirst%20into%20the%20world%20of%20investing.%20And%20while%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20pitfalls%20and%20missteps%20that%20could%20plague%20young%20people%20along%20the%20way%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20shaping%20up%20to%20be%20the%20most%20financially%20savvy%20generation%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERise%20of%20retail%20investing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20deluge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F90830832%2Fgen-z-hardest-economic-challenges-experts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheadlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20Gen%20Z%20has%20it%20harder%20economically%20than%20any%20previous%20generation%2C%20how%20are%20they%20managing%20to%20save%20at%20rates%20that%20outpace%20their%20generational%20predecessors%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErin%20Lowry%2C%20author%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BBroke%20Millennial%26quot%3B%20book%20series%2C%20told%20me%20that%20%26quot%3Bso%20much%20of%20it%20is%20as%20simple%20as%20access.%26quot%3B%20Gen%20Z%20grew%20up%20online%2C%20long%20after%20the%20days%20of%20paper%20checks%20and%20physical%20credit-card%20imprinters.%20Money%20for%20the%20up-and-coming%20generation%20has%20always%20been%20digital.%20Instead%20of%20cash%2C%20there's%20Venmo%20and%20PayPal.%20Instead%20of%20a%20traditional%20brokerage%2C%20there%20are%20investing%20apps%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobinhood-collapse-what-happened-retail-investing-meme-stocks-future-finance-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobinhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Webull.%20Instead%20of%20a%20financial%20advisor%2C%20there%20are%20financial-planning%20channels%20on%20social-media%20platforms%20including%20YouTube%20and%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvesting%2C%20especially%2C%20has%20become%20far%20more%20democratized%20than%20it%20has%20for%20any%20generation%20prior%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowry%20said.%20%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20are%20the%20first%20digital%20natives%2C%20which%20also%20makes%20them%20uniquely%20more%20comfortable%20with%20things%20like%20investing%20via%20an%20app%20compared%20to%20previous%20generations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CFA%20Institute%20report%2C%2065%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20investors%20said%20they%20used%20investing%20apps%20to%20trade%2C%20while%20only%2055%25%20of%20millennials%20and%2038%25%20of%20Gen%20X%20investors%20said%20they%20used%20apps.%20Forty-eight%20percent%20of%20newly%20minted%20Gen%20Z%20investors%20said%20they%20were%20getting%20financial%20advice%20from%20social%20media%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20the%20CFA%20report%20said%2C%20these%20platforms%20are%20the%20%26quot%3Btop%20information%20source%26quot%3B%20for%20young%20investors%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20online%20tools%20lower%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20for%20many%20Gen%20Z%20investors%20and%20stand%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20deluge%20of%20forms%20and%20clunky%20customer%20service%20offered%20by%20traditional%20financial%20advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20older%20brokerage%20houses%20took%20a%20long%20time%20to%20adapt%20to%20have%20a%20decent%20app%20or%20even%20a%20decent%20interface%20on%20their%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowry%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20not%20really%20familiar%20with%20how%20investing%20works%2C%20it%20can%20be%20incredibly%20overwhelming%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20as%20simple%20as%20trying%20to%20open%20up%20a%20Roth%20IRA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFOMO%20investing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20access%20is%20what%20allows%20Gen%20Z%20to%20start%20investing%2C%20it's%20the%20online%20culture%20around%20money%20that%20drives%20them%20to%20jump%20in.%20For%20every%20scroll%20on%20social%20media%2C%20there%20is%20an%20ocean%20of%20financial%20influencers%2C%20%26quot%3Bfinfluencers%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20TikTok%2C%20YouTube%2C%20and%20Reddit%20ready%20to%20show%20you%20the%20three%20easy%20steps%20to%20make%20hundreds%2C%20or%20even%20thousands%2C%20of%20dollars.%20They%20rope%20in%20followers%20with%20scre