%20assets%20like%20nonfungible%20tokens%20and%20cryptocurrency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20going-for-broke%20mentally%20can%2C%20obviously%2C%20quickly%20turn%20sour.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20nearly%20total%20collapse%20of%20the%20crypto%20token%20luna%20triggered%20a%20substantial%20downturn%20in%20the%20overall%20cryptocurrency%20market.%20The%20estimated%20%2460%20billion%20wipeout%20caused%20many%20Gen%20Z%20investors%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fterra-luna-ust-cryptocurrency-crash-may-bitcoin-algorithmic-stablecoin-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elose%20big%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20then-23-year-old%20told%20Insider%20that%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-investing-crash-terra-luna-lost-life-savings-stablecoin-ust-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20their%20life%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20putting%20their%20money%20in%20the%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20where%20personal%20finance%20is%20personal%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20Price%2C%20a%20Gen%20Z%20founder%20and%20the%20chief%20experience%20officer%20of%20Savvy%2C%20an%20app%20that%20helps%20people%20maximize%20discounts%20on%20their%20purchases%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20see%20advice%20on%20social%20media%20that%20goes%20towards%20investing%20in%20a%20particular%20company%20or%20index%20funds%2C%20do%20your%20own%20due%20diligence%2C%20and%20take%20that%20as%20maybe%20a%20tip%20but%20not%20necessarily%20the%20do%20all%20be%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20in%20the%20generation%20is%20making%20bad%20investments.%20Price%20has%20noticed%20a%20lot%20of%20young%20investors%20simply%20putting%20their%20money%20behind%20their%20own%20likes%20and%20interests%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20boon%20for%20those%20companies.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20like%20Chipotle%2C%20they're%20investing%20in%20Chipotle%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Gen%20Z%20may%20not%20always%20be%20drawn%20to%20the%20safest%20investment%20choices%2C%20it's%20certainly%20getting%20some%20hands-on%20learning.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20going%20to%20lose%20money%20sometimes%2C%20and%20that%20should%20be%20a%20learning%20lesson%20to%20improve%20upon%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowry%20said.%20%26quot%3BBetter%20to%20be%20making%20those%20mistakes%20at%2019%20than%20at%2045%20or%2050.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaving%20for%20the%20future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20some%20members%20of%20Gen%20Z%20are%20falling%20for%20classic%20investing%20pitfalls%2C%20many%20young%20people%20are%20taking%20a%20sound%20approach%20to%20financial%20planning.%20In%20particular%2C%20they%20are%20learning%20from%20their%20parents'%20mistakes%20and%20getting%20a%20head%20start%20on%20their%20retirement%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20started%20saving%20for%20retirement%20at%20the%20median%20age%20of%2019%2C%20earlier%20than%20any%20other%20generation%2C%20the%20Transamerica%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20Studies%20survey%20found.%20And%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.vanguard.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fcorp%2Fresearch%2Fpdf%2Fgenerational_changes_in_401(k)_behaviors.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20compared%20with%20people%20entering%20the%20workplace%20just%2015%20years%20prior%2C%20Gen%20Z%20seemed%20to%20have%20learned%20some%20lessons%3A%2062%25%20of%2018-%20to%2024-year-olds%20said%20they%20were%20contributing%20to%20their%20workplace%20retirement%20plan%20in%202021%2C%20compared%20with%2030%25%20of%20people%20who%20were%20the%20same%20age%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPastor%2C%20the%20Motley%20Fool%20expert%2C%20believes%20this%20is%20partly%20due%20to%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20employers%20who%20are%20auto-enrolling%20workers%20in%20retirement%20plans.%20But%20it's%20also%20a%20result%20of%20how%20out-of-reach%20retirement%20feels%20for%20many%20young%20adults%2C%20pushing%20them%20to%20start%20saving%20as%20early%20as%20possible.%20Seeing%20the%20financial%20pressure%20that%20saving%20for%20retirement%20has%20put%20on%20her%20parents%20and%20grandparents%20was%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20an%20awakening%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20working%20until%20I'm%2065%2C%2070%20years%20old.%20I%20want%20to%20enjoy%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%20The%20number%20of%20workers%20unsure%20they'll%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20retire%20has%20grown%20from%2032%25%20in%202021%20to%2044%25%20in%202023%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackrock.com%2Fus%2Findividual%2Finsights%2Fretirement%2F2023-read-on-retirement-survey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlackRock%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%2C%20with%20just%2056%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20saying%20they%20expected%20to%20reach%20the%20milestone.%20Pastor%20believes%20the%20pessimism%20is%20due%20to%20residual%20fear%20from%20the%202008%20and%202020%20financial%20crashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20forcing%20young%20savers%20to%20really%20take%20the%20reins%20and%20be%20advocates%20for%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20nobody%20else%20is%20going%20to%20step%20in%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20they%20feel%20comfortable%20with%20investing%20or%20saving%20for%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20respects%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-won-pandemic-recovery-gen-z-class-of-2019-economy-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20is%20coming%20of%20age%20at%20a%20good%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20graduating%20into%20a%20booming%20job%20market%20with%20strong%20wage%20growth.%20By%20contrast%2C%20millennials'%20journey%20to%20adulthood%20was%20riddled%20with%20obstacles%2C%20including%20two%20recessions%20before%20the%20age%20of%2040%20that%20came%20with%20widespread%20job%20losses%2C%20home%20foreclosures%2C%20and%20investment%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sheer%20number%20of%20millennials%20that%20I%20know%20who%20would%20not%20invest%20because%20they%20were%20so%20scared%20of%20it%20because%20of%202008%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowry%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bintense%20scarcity%20mindset%26quot%3B%20among%20her%20generation%20of%20millennials.%20She%20said%20that%20many%20thought%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20have%20money%2C%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20save%20it.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20put%20any%20risks%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20had%20the%20chance%20to%20learn%20from%20their%20elders%20and%20use%20a%20deluge%20of%20online%20resources%20to%20make%20their%20money%20grow.%20Whether%20it's%20the%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20on%20big%20investment%20gains%20or%20the%20fear%20of%20not%20having%20enough%20money%20to%20retire%2C%20Gen%20Z%20heard%20the%20financial%20advice%20%26quot%3Bstart%20early%26quot%3B%20and%20ran%20with%20it.%20And%20with%20time%20on%20their%20side%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20in%20for%20a%20penny%2C%20in%20for%20a%20pound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feve-upton-clark%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEve%20Upton-Clark%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20features%20writer%20covering%20culture%20and%20society.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-financially-savvy-generation-retirement-saving-investing-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699267561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6545460836d588dc55caaf63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-financially-savvy-generation-retirement-saving-investing-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today's%20young%20investors%20are%20already%20way%20better%20with%