i%3EHe%20writes%20that%20managers%20lost%20some%20control%20of%20their%20employees%20when%20people%20started%20working%20from%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20advises%20managers%20to%20ask%20how%20an%20employee%20is%20performing%20if%20they%20discover%20the%20worker%20has%20two%20jobs.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20world%20was%20abruptly%20forced%20to%20work%20from%20home%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20shook%20many%20managers%20to%20their%20core.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20lifelong%20student%20of%20management%20and%20a%20leader%20for%20over%2040%20years%2C%20including%20being%20the%20VP%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft.%20The%20introduction%20of%20work-from-home%20was%20a%20fascinating%20time%20because%20it%20gave%20me%20a%20chance%20to%20see%20abject%20fear%20on%20the%20faces%20of%20managers%20because%20they%20suddenly%20lost%20the%20very%20control%20they%20had%20lived%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EManagers%20lost%20control%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20now%20working%20from%20home%20were%20relieved%20of%20a%20commute%2C%20office%20distractions%2C%20and%20the%20hawk%20eye%20of%20their%20managers.%20Most%20transitioned%20effectively%2C%20and%20many%20thrived.%20But%20some%20took%20advantage%20of%20their%20newfound%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20writhed%20in%20horror%20at%20the%20lack%20of%20control.%20They%20shared%20viral%20stories%20of%20employees%20spending%20their%20days%20playing%20video%20games%2C%20working%20from%20the%20beach%2C%20or%20the%20ultimate%20horror%3A%20working%20two%20full-time%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%20last%20year%2C%20several%20news%20outlets%20ran%20breathless%20stories%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20programmers%20making%20over%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20a%20year%20working%20multiple%20full-time%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20juggling%20Zoom%20calls%20and%20multiple%20deadlines%20from%20their%20home%20office%20to%20%26quot%3Bcheat%26quot%3B%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shock%20value%20was%20clear%20to%20many%20managers%3A%20these%20employees%20were%20getting%20away%20with%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20multiple%20jobs%20is%20common%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20who%20also%20works%20two%20jobs%3F%20The%20bottom%20third%20of%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20cashier%20at%20Target%20who%20also%20drives%20for%20Uber%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20a%20schoolteacher%20who%20cleans%20offices%20on%20the%20weekend%2C%20a%20McDonald's%20cook%20who%20tends%20bar%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20multiple%20jobs%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20fabric%20of%20the%20working%20world%20%E2%80%94%20so%20common%20that%20it's%20in%20the%20origin%20stories%20of%20many%20successful%20people.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20worked%20two%20jobs%20to%20put%20us%20kids%20through%20college.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20freedom%20of%20place%20granted%20by%20work-from-home%20made%20this%20option%20available%20to%20more%20workers.%20It%20even%20sprouted%20an%20online%20community%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foveremployed.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOveremployed.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20how-to%20articles%20and%20people%20sharing%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20work%20multiple%20jobs%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20168%20hours%20in%20a%20week%2C%20an%20eager%20or%20financially%20struggling%20employee%20sees%20a%20single%2040-hour%20job%20as%20a%20poor%20use%20of%20time.%20It's%20unrealistic%20to%20expect%20them%20to%20use%20but%2025%25%20of%20their%20week%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20or%20to%20get%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20unrealistic%20as%20it%20is%20for%20managers%20to%20think%20their%20claim%20to%20employees'%20time%20is%20exclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%2C%20the%20message%20is%20clear%3A%20You%20don't%20own%20your%20employee's%20lives.%20What%20they%20choose%20to%20do%20when%20not%20working%20for%20you%20is%20simply%20none%20of%20your%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20managers%20should%20handle%20a%20double%20dipper%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20manager%20who%20discovers%20an%20employee%20is%20also%20working%20elsewhere%2C%20how%20you%20react%20is%20crucial.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-managers-react-employee-working-two-full-time-jobs-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20many%20ways%20to%20handle%20it%2C%20and%20the%20managers'%20reactions%20vary%20widely.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20are%20competitive%20concerns.%20An%20employee%20working%20for%20a%20competitor%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20worse%2C%20leveraging%20confidential%20information%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20problem.%20As%20an%20employer%2C%20you%20have%20some%20rights%20to%20enforce%20non-compete%20and%20confidentiality%20restrictions%20(although%20those%20vary%20by%20state%20or%20country%20and%20are%20complicated%20by%20remote%20arrangements).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20outside%20of%20that%2C%20an%20employee%20using%20their%20time%20or%20skills%20to%20make%20additional%20income%20comes%20down%20to%20one%20simple%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20are%20they%20performing%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20management%20issue%20is%20the%20same%20as%20it%20always%20is%3A%20how%20is%20the%20employee%20performing%20in%20their%20job%3F%20Are%20they%20getting%20the%20job%20%E2%80%94%20your%20job%20%E2%80%94%20done%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20employee%20is%20underperforming%2C%20address%20the%20deficit.%20Hold%20them%20accountable%20for%20their%20deliverables.%20Press%20them%20to%20provide%20the%20value%20you're%20paying%20them%20for.%20Treat%20it%20as%20you%20would%20any%20other%20performance%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20they%20are%20doing%20outside%20of%20work%20that%20might%20be%20causing%20a%20performance%20problem%20is%2C%20again%2C%20none%20of%20your%20business.%20Your%20response%20should%20be%3A%20I%20expect%20and%20am%20paying%20for%20these%20results%2C%20you're%20not%20delivering%2C%20let's%20solve%20that%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20the%20employee%20is%20doing%20well%2C%20even%20excelling%2C%20you%20can%20choose%20your%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20could%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1)%20Throw%20a%20fit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20managers%20immediately%20overreact.%20They%20insist%20the%20employee%20cease%20all%20other%20work.%20They%20are%20outraged%20at%20the%20disloyalty%2C%20shocked%20by%20the%20hubris%2C%20and%20even%20personally%20offended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20end%20well.%20If%20the%20employee%20is%20doing%20your%20job%20well%20and%20isn't%20working%20for%20a%20competitor%2C%20they%20are%20well%20within%20their%20rights.%20An%20overreaction%20destroys%20any%20relationship%20you%20might%20have%2C%20and%20likely%20demotivates%20them%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20reaction%20has%20turned%20a%20high-performing%20employee%20into%20the%20enemy%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20almost%20certainly%20looking%20for%20the%20exit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2)%20Increase%20their%20workload%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20managers%20react%20by%20increasing%20the%20work.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20time%20to%20work%20for%20someone%20else%2C%20you%20can%20do%20more%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%20they're%20doing%20what%20is%20expected%20to%20a%20level%20that%20is%20clearly%20satisfactory%2C%20or%20at%20least%20was%20satisfactory%20until%20you%20discovered%20their%20other%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20their%20workload%20will%20likely%20decrease%20their%20performance.%20It%20will%20certainly%20lay%20waste%20to%20their%20attitude%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20doesn't%20come%20with%20additional%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20again%2C%20your%20reaction%20has%20turned%20a%20high%20performer%20against%20you.%20You've%20made%20a%20good%20situation%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou've%20also%20encouraged%20them%20to%20look%20elsewhere.%20They%20found%20a%20second%20job%3B%20finding%20a%20replacement%20for%20yours%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20much%20of%20a%20stretch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3)%20Celebrate%20their%20success%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20mature%20approach%20is%20to%20celebrate%20their%20success.%20Especially%20if%20they%20are%20a%20very%20high%20performer%2C%20you%20should%20reward%20their%20performance%20and%20acknowledge%20their%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20acknowledge%20their%20second%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20reward%20their%20success%2C%20even%20increase%20their%20pay%2C%20you%20enhance%20their%20experience.%20They%20feel%20recognized%20and%20supported.%20You%20look%20like%20an%20enlightened%20leader%2C%20one%20who%20knows%20and%20acknowledges%20a%20good%20thing%20when%20they%20have%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20will%20increase%20the%20employee's%20appreciation%20for%20your%20job%20and%20your%20leadership.%20Their%20performance%20might%20well%20increase.%20You%20might%20even%20make%20them%20abandon%20their%20second%20job%2C%20because%20it's%20now%20unnecessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4)%20Share%20the%20wealth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20you%20can%20learn%20from%20these%20overachievers.%20If%20their%20performance%20is%20exceptional%2C%20find%20out%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20multiple-job%20workers%20are%20models%20to%20be%20studied.%20They%20are%20figuring%20out%20ways%20to%20do%20a%20week's%20worth%20of%20work%20in%20three%20days.%20They%20are%20unbothered%20by%20complex%2C%20competing%20priorities.%20They%20are%2C%20by%20necessity%2C%20multitasking%2C%20and%20are%20job%20efficiency%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20reaction%20shouldn't%20be%2C%20%26quot%3BGreat%2C%20let's%20give%20you%20five%20days'%20worth%20of%20work%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20noted%20in%20number%20two%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20it%20should%20be%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20teach%20everyone%20how%20you're%20doing%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20if%20you%20had%20a%20whole%20team%20of%20people%20who%20could%20perform%20at%20that%20level%20%E2%80%94%20who%20could%20be%20more%20efficient%2C%20juggle%20competing%20priorities%2C%20be%20unaffected%20by%20distractions%3F%20You%20could%20increase%20throughput%20individually%2C%20and%20vastly%20increase%20the%20whole%20team's%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20chastise%20the%20moonlighter%2C%20celebrate%20the%20innovation%20of%20that%20performer.%20Acknowledge%20their%20creativity.%20And%20have%20them%20help%20the%20whole%20team%20excel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYour%20reaction%20is%20key%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20manager%20and%20discover%20an%20employee%20is%20working%20another%20job%20on%20the%20side%2C%20how%20you%20react%20is%20key.%20Whether%20it's%20work-from-home%20or%20not%2C%20what%20matters%20is%20their%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20are%20struggling%2C%20address%20the%20problem.%20If%20they're%20not%20meeting%20expectations%2C%20find%20a%20way%20to%20address%20the%20performance%20problem.%20And%20no%2C%20quitting%20the%20second%20job%20is%20not%20the%20first%20thing%20on%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20are%20meeting%20expectations%2C%20even%20excelling%2C%20your%20reaction%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%20You%20have%20an%20employee%20doing%20good%20work%20and%20getting%20fairly%20compensated%20for%20that%20work.%20Do%20not%20spoil%20that%20with%20your%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they're%20doing%20well%2C%20tell%20them%20so.%20If%20they%20are%20doing%20amazingly%20well%2C%20have%20them%20tell%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%2C%20your%20team%2C%20and%20the%20employee%20will%20all%20be%20better%20off%20if%20you%20handle%20it%20with%20grace%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%2C%20you%20are%20participating%20in%20a%20fair%20exchange%3A%20they%20give%20you%20their%20time%2C%20you%20get%20their%20results.%20What%20happens%20beyond%20that%20is%20not%20your%20business.%20A%20smart%20leader%20recognizes%20the%20situation%20and%20tries%20to%20make%20it%20work%20well%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clwill.com%2