6jv%253D15.4.2-stackpath%2526sref%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.popsci.com%25252Fscience%25252Fstarfish-head-body%25252F%2526url%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.nature.com%25252Farticles%25252Fs41586-023-06669-2%2526xs%253D1%2526xtz%253D240%2526xuuid%253Dfdbbcead664a49c755cc7210707c6722%2526xcust%253Dxid%25253Afr1699038560077jie%2526xjsf%253Dother_click__contextmenu%252520%25255B2%25255D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20has%20been%20centuries%20in%20the%20making.%20It's%20a%20mystery%20that%20%26quot%3Bdates%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%20of%20zoology%2C%26quot%3B%20Laurent%20Formery%2C%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20it%20took%20centuries%20to%20identify%20a%20starfish%20head%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFormery%2C%20who%20is%20a%20postdoc%20at%20Stanford%20School%20of%20Humanities%20and%20Sciences%2C%20said%20it%20took%20so%20long%20to%20solve%20this%20mystery%20because%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20really%20because%20they%20are%20so%20different%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20sea%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222282%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gettyimages.com%2Fdetail%2Fphoto%2Fholding-a-starfish-at-touch-pool-in-coral-world-royalty-free-image%2F529593712%3Fphrase%3Dstarfish%26amp%3Badppopup%3Dtrue%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65486238b788914e5550a44b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDespite%20appearances%2C%20starfish%20are%20more%20similar%20to%20humans%20than%20meets%20the%20eye.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Guttman%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20animals%20like%20insects%2C%20reptiles%2C%20birds%2C%20and%20mammals%20%E2%80%94%20including%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20have%20what's%20called%20bilateral%20symmetry%2C%20which%20means%20they're%20symmetric%20along%20a%20midline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20helps%20scientists%20identify%20the%20location%20of%20the%20head%2C%20trunk%2C%20limbs%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20Formery%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20sea%20stars%20with%20five%20limbs%2C%20lack%20bilateral%20symmetry%20and%20instead%20have%20what's%20called%20five-fold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-discover-new-species-of-feather-stars-with-20-arms-2023-8%5C%22%3Eradial%20symmetry%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fstarfish-have-feet-2017-2%5C%22%3Elook%20at%20a%20sea%20star%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20nothing%20that%20looks%20like%20your%20head.%20You%20just%20have%20no%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20Formery%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20appearances%2C%20however%2C%20sea%20stars%20actually%20have%20more%20genetically%20in%20common%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomparing-genetic-similarity-between-humans-and-other-things-2016-5%5C%22%3Eanimals%20like%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20meets%20the%20eye%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.stanford.edu%2F2023%2F11%2F01%2Fstudy-reveals-location-starfishs-head%2F%3Futm_source%3Dfeedotter%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Dext-11-01-2023%26utm_content%3Dhttpsnewsstanfordedu20231101studyrevealslocationstarfishshead%26mkt_tok%3DNjYwLVRKQy05ODQAAAGPLxt_PQi_raGV7a2l8p9I6Lzqx6NPTFiOo8zuAC4QFHuTQETFJgHfcgZm337_wzkhiLzQraKfkjfYk71yhamtw_tEYHOoSqmgX0mRXA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanford%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMapping%20a%20starfish's%20genetic%20code%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fage-of-genetically-engineered-animals-has-arrived-2015-6%5C%22%3EAnimals%20have%20a%20genetic%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20unfurls%20and%20activates%20different%20regions%20as%20we%20develop%20%E2%80%94%20sticking%20a%20leg%20here%2C%20an%20arm%20there%2C%20and%20a%20head%20over%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20those%20genetic%20similarities%20that%20Formery%20and%20his%20colleagues%20studied.%20But%20they%20couldn't%20have%20done%20it%20without%20the%20help%20of%20modern%20technology%2C%20Formery%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20pink%20starfish%20with%20black%20dots.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6548608936d588dc55cb2de5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStarfish%20are%20far%20more%20complex%20than%20scientists%20ever%20imagined.%3Cp%3Eantpkr%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%20we%20just%20had%20access%20to%20anatomy%20and%20morphology.%20And%20they're%20not%20very%20helpful%20when%20you%20look%20at%20a%20sea%20star%2C%26quot%3B%20Formery%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20recently%2C%20we%20can%20kind%20of%20ignore%20the%20morphology%20and%20just%20focus%20on%20the%20molecular%20aspects%20of%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20analyzed%20the%20different%20genes%20within%20individual%20starfish%20limbs.%20Initially%2C%20they%20were%20expecting%20to%20find%20some%20genes%20that%20resembled%20a%20head%20and%20some%20that%20resembled%20a%20trunk%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20most%20animals.%20But%2C%20instead%2C%20they%20found%20mostly%20head-like%20genes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20genes%20that%20are%20typically%20involved%20in%20the%20patterning%20of%20the%20trunk%20of%20the%20animal%20weren't%20expressed%20in%20the%20ectoderm.%20It%20seems%20the%20whole%20echinoderm%20body%20plan%20is%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20head%20in%20other%20groups%20of%20animals%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20co-author%20Jeff%20Thompson%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southampton%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southampton.ac.uk%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2Fstarfish-body-head.page%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20weird%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20unexpected%2C%20Formery%20added.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20really%20had%20%5Bthis%5D%20envisioned%20before%20we%20had%20access%20to%20this%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDo%20starfish%20have%20a%20brain%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20Formery%20said%20that%20he's%20interested%20in%20analyzing%20the%20starfish%20more%20to%20determine%20whether%20its%20multiple%20heads%20may%20also%20contain%20multiple%20brains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20look%20at%20textbooks%2C%20they%20say%20sea%20stars%20have%20a%20very%20simple%20nervous%20system%2C%20and%20it's%20like%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20brain%2C%26quot%3B%20Formery%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhich%20is%20interesting%2C%20because%20the%20studies%20that%20we%20did%20suggest%20that%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20nervous%20system%20of%20a%20starfish%2C%26quot%3B%20some%20of%20the%20genes%20that%20give%20rise%20to%20its%20nervous%20system%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bthe%20genes%20that%20are%20involved%20during%20our%20own%20development%20to%20make%20the%20brain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20raises%20very%20interesting%20questions%20about%20what%20is%20the%20nervous%20system%20of%20a%20sea%20star%3F%20And%20is%20it%20a%20brain%3F%20Is%20it%20just%20a%20brain%20basically%3F%26quot%3B%20Formery%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarfish-have-multiple-heads-scientists-discover-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699263802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654861753cc84b4dfafcc416%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarfish-have-multiple-heads-scientists-discover-2023