d%20edition%20launched%20in%20August%202019%20was%20for%202017-18.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20published%20by%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20was%20prepared%20in%20association%20with%20three%20ministries%20%E2%80%93%20Water%20Resources%2C%20Drinking%20Water%20%26amp%3B%20Sanitation%2C%20and%20Rural%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20apex%20government%20policy%20think%20tank%20wrote%20to%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti%2C%20seeking%20their%20perspective%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cuse%20and%20applicability%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20report%20and%20whether%20the%20CWMI%20should%20continue.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3ENo%20response%20was%20received%20from%20the%20ministry%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20editions%20await%20release%2C%20the%20paper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20NITI%20Aayog%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20reports%20may%20be%20clubbed%20with%20those%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years%20(2020%20and%202021).%20There%20have%20also%20been%20talks%20of%20other%20channels%20being%20explored%20for%20the%20task%20of%20indexing%20instead%20of%20sole%20reliance%20on%20the%20CWMI%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20discussed%20in%20a%20meeting%20between%20NITI%20Aayog%20member%20Ramesh%20Chand%20and%20officers%20of%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%20on%20December%2012%2C%202022.%20Nearly%20five%20months%20after%20this%20meeting%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20sent%20letters%20to%20Department%20of%20Water%20Resources%2C%20River%20Development%20and%20Ganga%20Rejuvenation%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Drinking%20Water%20and%20Sanitation%2C%20both%20of%20which%20come%20under%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Member%20(economist%20Ramesh%20Chand)%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20other%20channels%20need%20to%20be%20explored%20to%20undertake%20the%20task%20of%20indexing%20rather%20than%20relying%20only%20on%20CWMI%20and%20that%20the%20CWMI%20is%20not%20widely%20used%20or%20applied%20in%20Planning%2C%20Decision%20making%2C%20Policy%20Formulation%20or%20Research%20by%20public%20or%20private%20stakeholders%20concerned%20with%20water%20sector%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Indian%20Express%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20which%20has%20been%20seen%20by%20paper%2C%20points%20out%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fniti-weighs-discontinuing-key-water-report-launched-5-years-ago-9015084%2F%5C%22%3Ewater%20scarcity%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20problem%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20Jal%20Shakti%20Ministry%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20per%20capita%20water%20availability%20is%20projected%20to%20decline%20to%201%2C486%20cubic%20meters%20per%20person%20per%20year%20by%202021%20as%20compared%20to%201%2C545%20cubic%20meters%20per%20person%20per%20year%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20accordance%20with%20the%20annual%20water%20availability%20norms%2C%20a%20value%20below%201%2C700%20cubic%20meter%2Fperson%2Fyear%20indicates%20water%20shortage%20while%20that%20below%201%2C000%20cubic%20metre%2Fcapita%2Fyear%20is%20considered%20as%20%E2%80%9Cscarcity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20been%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20suppressing%20data%20that%20may%20prove%20electorally%20unfavourable.%20In%20the%20past%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-data-npr-nrc-economy%5C%22%3Edelayed%20the%20release%20of%20data%20or%20claimed%20that%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20key%20factors%20like%20unemployment%2