re%20at%201800-110-332.%20You%20can%20also%20check%20the%20DDA's%20official%20website%20for%20detailed%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERemember%20to%20save%20your%20application%20number%20for%20future%20reference.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699257180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-01%2Fdda-flats_650x400_61514915861.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdda-diwali-special-housing-scheme-2023-heres-what-you-need-to-know-4549302%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20DDA%20Housing%20Scheme%202023%20will%20allow%20potential%20buyers%20to%20acquire%20apartments%20at%20various%20locations%2C%20including%20Delhi%2C%20Ghaziabad%2C%20Noida%2C%20and%20Greater%20Noida.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdda-diwali-special-housing-scheme-2023-heres-what-you-need-to-know-4549302%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98The%20Difference%20Between%20Then%20and%20Now%E2%80%99%3A%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20on%20Emergency%20and%20the%20Modi%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06131557%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-1.15.11%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESeptember%2025%2C%201975.%20It%20was%20not%20the%20usual%20campus%20morning%20at%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU).%20A%20strike%20called%20by%20the%20Students%20Federation%20of%20India%20(SFI)%20to%20protest%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Ashoklata%20Jain%20%E2%80%94%20an%20elected%20councillor%20of%20the%20students%20union%20%E2%80%94%20was%20in%20its%20second%20day%20and%20the%20campus%20was%20tense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20three%20months%20since%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20declared%20a%20state%20of%20Emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20was%20on%20the%20lawns%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Languages%20that%20morning%2C%20with%20a%20few%20friends%20from%20the%20SFI%2C%20when%20a%20black%20Ambassador%20stopped%20near%20us%20and%20a%20burly%20man%20got%20out.%20He%20came%20up%20to%20me%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20was%20D.P.%20Tripathi%20%E2%80%94%20then%20president%20of%20the%20students%20union.%20I%20replied%20that%20I%20was%20not%2C%20but%20my%20questioner%20was%20a%20cop%2C%20DIG-Range%20P.S.%20Bhinder%2C%20and%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20me.%20He%20and%20his%20men%2C%20all%20in%20plainclothes%2C%20swiftly%20proceeded%20to%20kidnap%20me%20in%20broad%20daylight.%20I%20would%20end%20up%20in%20jail%2C%20kept%20there%20for%20a%20year%20under%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Internal%20Security%20Act%20(MISA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20370px)%2085vw%2C%20370px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22370%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front.jpg%20776w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front-194x300.jpg%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front-662x1024.jpg%20662w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683676%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22572%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrabir%20Purkayastha%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EKeeping%20Up%20the%20Good%20Fight%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ELeftWord%20Books%20(October%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20by%20five%20decades.%20The%20government%20led%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20have%20been%20in%20power%20since%202014.%20They%20won%20a%20second%20term%20in%202019.%20The%20India%20we%20knew%2C%20that%20we%20thought%20of%20as%20home%2C%20was%20being%20changed%20by%20the%20day%2C%20in%20myriad%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFebruary%209%2C%202021.%20Morning%20again.%20I%20was%20at%20home.%20I%20had%20just%20finished%20breakfast%20and%20was%20reading%20the%20newspapers%20when%20the%20doorbell%20rang.%20It%20was%20a%20group%20of%20men%2C%20one%20of%20them%20with%20an%20official-looking%20paper%20in%20hand.%20They%20were%20from%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20he%20announced.%20The%20ED%20was%20here%20to%20conduct%20a%20raid.%20Their%20target%20was%20NewsClick%2C%20the%20digital%20web%20platform%20I%20had%20set%20up%20in%202009%2C%20and%20which%20had%20grown%20over%20the%20years%20in%20terms%20of%20both%20its%20work%20and%20its%20viewership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20raid%20continued%20through%20almost%20five%20days%20or%20113%20hours%2C%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20raids%20of%20a%20private%20residence.%20The%20record%2C%20as%20I%20would%20come%20to%20learn%2C%20is%20held%20by%20a%20raid%20lasting%20nearly%20ten%20days.%20It%20had%20taken%20place%20at%20the%20Jaigarh%20Fort%20of%20Rajmata%20Gayatri%20Devi%20%E2%80%94%20a%20place%20covering%20three%20square%20kilometres%2C%20somewhat%20larger%20than%20my%20second-floor%20flat.%20But%20no%2C%20the%20ED%20was%20not%20busy%20searching%20my%20flat%20all%20the%20time%20they%20were%20there%3B%20they%20could%20have%20easily%20finished%20within%20a%20few%20hours.%20Except%20that%20they%20had%20a%20%E2%80%98high-tech%E2%80%99%20problem%3A%20how%20were%20they%20to%20download%20my%20voluminous%20data%20from%20Google%3F%20Since%20Google%20throttles%20the%20speed%20of%20downloads%20beyond%20a%20certain%20limit%2C%20the%20downloading%20becomes%20excruciatingly%20slow%20after%20a%20few%20hours.%20My%20poor%20digital%20housekeeping%20had%20created%20a%20problem%20for%20the%20ED%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20for%20me.%20Hosting%20the%20ED%2C%20or%20any%20agency%20of%20the%20state%2C%20for%20almost%20five%20days%20is%20going%20beyond%20the%20call%20of%20hospitality%2C%20to%20put%20it%20mildly!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20earlier%20%E2%80%98emergency%20encounter%E2%80%99%20was%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20students%E2%80%99%20resistance%20in%20JNU.%20D.P.%20Tripathi%2C%20Ashoklata%20(usually%20called%20Ashoka)%2C%20Sitaram%20(Yechury)%20and%20others%20were%20among%20the%20key%20figures%20in%20that%20resistance.%20My%20encounter%20in%20the%20current%20%E2%80%98emergency%E2%80%99%20took%20place%20in%20rather%20different%20circumstances.%20NewsClick%2C%20a%20relatively%20small%20outfit%2C%20was%20somehow%20perceived%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98problem%E2%80%99.%20Perhaps%20the%20problem%20was%20not%20so%20much%20NewsClick%20as%20the%20range%20of%20movements%20it%20covers.%20Just%20prior%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20unwelcome%20attention%2C%20NewsClick%20had%20covered%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%20quite%20thoroughly%2C%20coverage%20that%20drew%20significant%20viewership%2C%20and%20not%20just%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20again%2C%20NewsClick%20was%20not%2C%20and%20is%20not%2C%20unique%20in%20its%20coverage.%20Many%20other%20digital%20platforms%2C%20and%20even%20certain%20mainstream%20media%2C%20have%20covered%20assaults%20on%20people%2C%20livelihood%20and%20reason%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20public%20protests%20that%20take%20place%20in%20response.%20Like%20us%2C%20some%20of%20these%20media%20organisations%20are%20very%20much%20under%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20scanner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20want%20to%20go%20into%20the%20various%20cases%20that%20NewsClick%20and%20I%20continue%20to%20face%3B%20or%20the%20campaign%20unleashed%20against%20us%20by%20a%20hounding%20variety%20of%20media.%20The%20legal%20matters%20are%20in%20the%20courts%20and%20we%20will%20fight%20the%20cases%20there.%20I%20have%20no%20desire%20to%20become%20the%20news.%20Nor%20does%20NewsClick%3B%20its%20job%20is%20to%20cover%20the%20news.%20It%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20what%20it%20has%20done%20from%20the%20time%20it%20was%20set%20up%3A%20follow%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20amplify%20the%20voices%20of%20those%20who%20are%20rarely%20heard%20in%20our%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20difference%20between%20then%20and%20now%20is%20at%20the%20fundamental%20level%20of%20ideology.%20The%20Congress%20ideology%20did%20not%20view%20certain%20sections%20of%20the%20people%20as%20outsiders%2C%20to%20be%20treated%20either%20as%20second-class%20citizens%20or%20excluded%20from%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%202014%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20dramatic%20increase%20in%20what%20we%20can%20only%20call%20hate%20crimes.%20Muslims%20have%20been%20the%20target%20in%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20these%20crimes%3B%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%20and%20women%20form%20part%20of%20the%20list%20as%20well%2C%20as%20do%20secular%20activists.%20Was%20it%20the%20same%20situation%20during%20the%20Emergency%3F%20Yes%2C%20there%20was%20oppression%3B%20but%20it%20was%20secular%20oppression.%20Yes%2C%20there%20was%20the%20Turkman%20Gate%20incident%20during%20the%20Emergency%2C%20when%20Muslims%20(and%20other%20residents%20of%20the%20area)%20were%20attacked.%20This%20incident%20illustrates%20a%20particular%20toxic%20combination%20of%20the%20Emergency%20agenda%3A%20family%20planning%20in%20the%20form%20of%20vasectomy%2C%20and%20demolition%20of%20poor%20areas%20to%20prettify%20the%20city.%20(Family%20planning%20expressed%20the%20fear%20of%20the%20middle%20classes%20that%20the%20poor%20were%20breeding%20too%20much%2C%20a%20favourite%20bugbear%20in%20the%20West%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20population%20growth%20of%20countries%20like%20India%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20their%20control%20over%20the%20globe%E2%80%99s%20resources.)%20But%20overall%2C%20the%20Emergency%20government%20was%20not%20trying%20to%20exclude%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIdeologically%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20not%20following%20the%20Savarkar%20thesis%20which%20plays%20out%20today%20both%20formally%20and%20informally%3A%20Minorities%20can%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20but%20only%20as%20second-class%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20not%20what%20the%20Congress%20ideology%20was.%20Nor%20what%20the%20national%20movement%20had%20built%3B%20certainly%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20not%20publicly%20espouse%20such%20an%20ideology.%20The%20Congress%20could%20and%20did%20say%20that%20the%20Emergency%20was%20a%20necessary%20interim%20period%20of%20%E2%80%98discipline%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20Vinoba%20Bhave%20put%20it%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20festival%20of%20discipline%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Eapaatkal%20ka%20anushaasan%20parv%3C%2Fem%3E).%20The%20Emergency%20was%20described%20as%20a%20short-period%20fix%3B%20whether%20this%20was%20the%20only%20intent%20or%20not%2C%20it%20was%20not%20translated%20into%20a%20structure%20within%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20seeing%20something%20different%20today.%20The%20structure%20of%20the%20state%20is%20apparently%20the%20same%3B%20but%20it%20is%20being%20hollowed%20out.%20There%20is%20an%20organised%20force%20that%20has%20risen%20to%20complement%20state%20power.%20This%20organised%20force%20takes%20on%20any%20resistance%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20people%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20compact%20between%20the%20state%20and%20this%20kind%20of%20intimidation%20politics.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20these%20forces%20do%20not%20comprise%20fringe%20elements%3B%20they%20are%20a%20significant%20political%20force%20in%20the%20country%2C%20they%20are%20%E2%80%98mainstream%E2%80%99.%20They%20help%20to%20build%20a%20kind%20of%20destructive%20and%20sectarian%20politics.%20The%20object%20is%20to%20exclude%20people%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20community%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20eroding%20the%20citizenship%20rights%20of%20some%20Indians.%20The%20Congress%20did%20not%20have%20all%20these%20exclusionary%20politics%20in%20its%20genetic%20composition%3B%20the%20RSS%20has%20them%20in%20its%20genes.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20crucial%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20difference%20between%20then%20and%20now%20is%20the%20sustained%20and%20multifarious%20attacks%20we%20see%20today%20on%20our%20secular%20ethos%2C%20on%20culture%2C%20on%20education%2C%20science%20and%20reason.%20This%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20part%20of%20the%20ideology-driven%20project%20of%20building%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20which%20will%20have%20little%20to%20do%20with%20the%20inclusive%2C%20secular%20nation%20with%20a%20scientific%20outlook%20envisioned%20by%20so%20many%20of%20our%20freedom%20fighters.%20The%20Hindutva%20brigade%20failed%20the%20national%20movement.%20They%20did%20not%20fight%20for%20independence.%20So%20their%20vision%20for%20India%20is%20to%20take%20it%20onto%20a%20different%20trajectory%20from%20the%20attempt%20in%201947%20which%20had%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20consensus%20among%20the%20people.%20Their%20battle%20was%20and%20has%20been%20against%20the%20Muslims.%20To%20put%20it%20another%20way%2C%20possibly%20a%20more%20precise%20way%2C%20it%20was%2C%20and%20is%2C%20for%20Hindu%20supremacy.%20The%20India%20they%20are%20fighting%20for%20will%20have%20one%20religion%20and%20one%20people%2C%20Hindi-Hindu-%20Hindu%20Rashtra%3B%20this%20means%20large%20numbers%20of%20Indians%20will%20become%20second-class%20citizens.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20Hindu%20supremacists%20are%20still%20fighting%20their%20battle%20in%20the%20past%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20by%20renaming%20streets%20and%20cities%2C%20pulling%20down%20monuments%2C%20or%20finding%20mandirs%20everywhere.%20The%20battle%20they%20are%20engaged%20in%20looks%20backwards%3B%20they%20have%20nothing%20to%20offer%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-279448%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%20and%20Indira-Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20we%20resist%20this%20new%20powerful%20Emergency%20without%20a%20name%3F%20I%20think%20we%20need%20a%20much%20larger%20coming%20together%20of%20people.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%20has%20been%20so%20important.%20In%20Western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Muslim%20and%20Jat%20farmers%20came%20together%20through%20the%20movement.%20To%20understand%20how%20significant%20this%20is%2C%20we%20have%20to%20recall%20that%20in%20September%202013%2C%20riots%20broke%20out%20between%20Muslims%20and%20Jats%20in%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20district.%20Several%20members%20of%20the%20BJP%20were%20accused%20of%20instigating%20the%20riots%3B%20and%20the%20BJP%20won%20the%20subsequent%20general%20and%20assembly%20elections%20from%20the%20region.%20The%20fracturing%20between%20the%20two%20communities%20that%20took%20place%20during%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20riots%20was%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20healed%20by%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMovements%20build%20this%20kind%20of%20unity.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20rightwing%20considers%20movements%20based%20on%20class%20issues%20dangerous%3A%20they%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20build%20on%20caste%20and%20community%20divisions%2C%20which%20is%20what%20the%20BJP%20does.%20Is%20it%20any%20surprise%20that%20movements%20%E2%80%94%20from%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movements%20and%20workers%E2%80%99%20movements%20to%20anti-caste%20movements%20and%20students%E2%80%99%20movements%20%E2%80%94%20become%20ideological%20threats%20to%20the%20RSS%20and%20the%20BJP%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Congress%20Emergency%2C%20the%20jailers%20were%20quite%20aware%20that%20some%20of%20the%20people%20they%20were%20holding%20in%20prison%20could%20well%20become%20the%20rulers%20someday.%20That%20was%20a%20clear%20motive%20to%20treat%20these%20prisoners%20differently.%20Mrs%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20government%20also%20accepted%20the%20fact%20that%20these%20prisoners%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98ordinary%E2%80%99%20people%20they%20had%20to%20%E2%80%98break%E2%80%99.%20Their%20plan%20of%20action%20was%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20media%20and%20its%20messaging%2C%20and%20to%20marginalise%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20methods%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20the%20overall%20plan%20to%20silence%20people%2C%20seems%20quite%20different%20today.%20The%20driving%20question%20seems%20to%20be%20How%20do%20we%20break%20the%20people%20who%20are%20standing%20up%20to%20us%3F%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20remould%20the%20state%20without%20these%20dissident%20voices%3B%20and%20ensure%20that%20nobody%20is%20able%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20the%20government%20or%20the%20right-wing%20forces%20in%20all%20their%20various%20avatars.%20This%20may%20explain%20some%20of%20the%20terrible%20pettiness%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20current%20regime%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20political%20prisoners.%20The%20most%20obvious%20example%20is%20that%20of%20Stan%20Swamy%2C%20the%2083-year-old%20activist%20who%20worked%20with%20Adivasis%20and%20who%20was%20jailed%20for%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20case.%20Here%20was%20a%20frail%20old%20man%20who%20suffered%20from%20various%20medical%20conditions%20including%20Parkinson%E2%80%99s.%20He%20had%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20sipper%20and%20straw%20because%20of%20the%20tremors%20in%20his%20hands.%20The%20NIA%20%E2%80%98sought%20time%E2%80%99%20to%20consider%20his%20request%3B%20a%20special%20court%20turned%20down%20the%20request.%20The%20activist%20had%20to%20make%20a%20fresh%20application%20for%20the%20sipper%20cup%20as%20well%20as%20winter%20clothes.%20Such%20banal%20acts%20of%20cruelty%2C%20such%20dehumanising%20acts%2C%20seem%20to%20carry%20a%20message%3A%20We%20can%20do%20anything%20we%20want%20to%20you%2C%20and%20no%20one%20can%20stop%20us.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20courts%20do%20not%20give%20political%20prisoners%20the%20protection%20they%20should%2C%20the%20message%20may%20well%20continue%20to%20hold%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOur%20hope%20is%20that%20as%20these%20flagrant%20violations%20of%20rights%20become%20more%20visible%2C%20more%20questions%20will%20also%20grow%20audible.%20One%20positive%20development%20is%20that%20the%20courts%20seem%20to%20be%20taking%20up%20more%20of%20these%20cases.%20Perhaps%20the%20ice%20is%20cracking%20a%20little%3F%20We%20will%20have%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Chr%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20excerpt%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EKeeping%20Up%20the%20Good%20Fight%3Cem%3E%20is%20republished%20with%20permission%20from%20LeftWord%20Books.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699257054000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06131557%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-1.15.11%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fdifference-then-and-now-prabir-purkayastha-book-excerpt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ideologically%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20not%20following%20the%20Savarkar%20thesis%20which%20plays%20out%20today%20both%20formally%20and%20informally%3A%20Minorities%20can%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20but%20only%20as%20second-class%20ci