l%20cyber%20attacks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2Findia-most-targeted-country-by-cyber-attackers-report%2Farticleshow%2F104989856.cms%23%3A~%3Atext%3DState%252Dsponsored%2520cyber%2520attacks%2520against%2Cthe%2520highest%2520share%2520of%2520attacks.%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20the%20second%20most%20targeted%20country%2C%20with%209.6%25%20of%20all%20attacks.%20Indonesia%20and%20China%20follow%2C%20with%209.3%25%20and%204.5%25%20of%20all%20attacks%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECyfirma%20founder%20and%20chief%20executive%20Kumar%20Ritesh%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20India%20is%20also%20experiencing%20a%20higher%20proportion%20of%20foreign%20state-influenced%20cyber%20attacks%20compared%20to%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20globally%2C%20almost%2068%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%20were%20state-sponsored.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20India%20number%2C%20this%20is%20slightly%20higher%2C%20at%2072%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECyfirma%20found%20that%20services%20companies%2C%20including%20IT%20and%20BPO%2C%20were%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%2014.3%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20between%20March%202021%20and%20September%202023.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20manufacturing%20at%2011.6%25%2C%20and%20healthcare%20and%20education%20at%20around%2010%25%20each.%20Retail%2C%20including%20online%20platforms%2C%20saw%209.8%25%20of%20attacks%20while%20government%20agencies%20saw%209.6%25.%20Banking%20and%20financial%20services%20institutions%2C%20automobiles%2C%20and%20airlines%20saw%209.5%25%2C%208.3%25%2C%20and%206.1%25%20of%20attacks%2C%20respectively%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202015-16%2C%2058-59%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20on%20India%20were%20from%20Pakistani%20threat%20actors%20or%20operators%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20he%20told%20the%20newspaper.%20Today%2C%20only%206.4%25%20of%20threats%20are%20from%20Pakistani%20actors%20or%20their%20affiliates%2C%20while%2079%25%20are%20from%20China%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20India%20needs%20a%20better%20enforcement%20of%20cybersecurity%20policies%20and%20greater%20awareness%2C%20especially%20among%20SMEs%20and%20startups%2C%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20sophisticated%20cybercriminals%20they%20are%20up%20against%2C%20Ritesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20as%20brand%20India%20are%20elevating%20ourselves%2C%20but%20it%20looks%20like%20cybercriminals%20are%20also%20elevating%20themselves%20because%20they%20know%20that%20we%20are%20becoming%20quite%20an%20influential%20force%20in%20the%20world%20ecosystem%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ritesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fnearly-60-of-healthcare-organisations-in-india-hit-by-cyberattacks-in-past-year-report%5C%22%3ENearly%2060%25%20Of%20Healthcare%20Organisations%20in%20India%20Hit%20by%20Cyberattacks%20in%20Past%20Year%3A%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20weakness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20digitisation%20has%20accelerated%20the%20need%20for%20cybersecurity%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20regulations%20are%20weak%20and%20inadequate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20on%20November%2030%2C%20the%20website%20of%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%20(ICMR)%20faced%20around%206%2C000%20hacking%20attempts%20in%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20happened%20a%20week%20after%20five%20servers%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Faiims-servers-cyberattack-ransomware-rajya-sabha%5C%22%3Ehad%20been%20hacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20ransomware.%20An%20estimated%201.3%20terabytes%20of%20data%20was%20encrypted.%20The%20hackers%20had%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20AIIMS%20to%20access%20its%20own%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2031%2C%202023%2C%20in%20a%20massive%20data%20breach%2C%20information%20of%20over%2081.5%20crore%20Indians%20with%20the%20ICMR%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fhealthcare%2Fnews-healthcare%2Fquestions-abound-but-icmr-still-silent-on-the-data-leak%2F3293107%2F%5C%22%3Ewere%20sold%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20dark%20web.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%20Technology%20Review%20CyberDefense%20Index%20(CDI)%202022%2F23%20ranked%20India%20at%20No.%2017%20out%20of%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMIT%E2%80%99s%20CDI%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98first-of-its-kind%E2%80%99%20annual%20comparative%20ranking%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%2020%20largest%20and%20most%20digital%20economies%20on%20their%20preparation%20against%2C%20and%20response%20and%20recovery%20from%2C%20cybersecurity%20threats%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcio.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fdigital-security%2Fcybersecurity-how-does-india-perform-at-the-global-stage%2F99628852%5C%22%3E%20another%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20struggles%2C%20despite%20a%20digitally%20forward%20government%20and%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20IT-enabled%20service%20sectors.%20This%20powerful%20tech%20force%20lacks%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20has%20poor%20national%20digital%20economy%20adoption%2C%20and%20weak%20cybersecurity%20regulation.%20Despite%20cyberattacks%20and%20calls%20for%20cybersecurity%20laws%20and%20a%20dedicated%20ministry%2C%20India%20has%20opted%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20report%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20number%20of%20cyberattacks%20has%20called%20for%20a%20cybersecurity%20law%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20dedicated%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20need%20for%20job%20creation%20in%20the%20cybersecurity%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20the%20second%20highest%20number%20of%20active%20internet%20users%20after%20China%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Findia-suffering-high-cybersecurity-skill-gap-40k-open-positions-report-123062100397_1.html%5C%22%3Erepresents%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%206%25%20of%20the%20global%20cybersecurity%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERajeev%20Sharma%2C%20CEO%20and%20CIO%2C%20Sysquark%20Technologies%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20an%20IT%20services%20company%20told%20the%20newspaper%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20would%20worry%20about%20theft%20when%20you%20have%20something%20to%20protect.%20Now%20think%20as%20a%20country%20instead%20of%20as%20a%20company.%20Companies%20will%20always%20have%20data%20to%20protect%20but%20they%20will%20always%20be%20short%20of%20resources.%20For%20a%20resource%2C%20security%20comes%20last%20in%20mind%20because%20he%20is%20busy%20doing%20firefighting.%20For%20a%20company%2C%20hiring%20more%20resources%20is%20not%20cost-effective%20since%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20customers%20are%20planning%20to%20buy%20the%20services%2Fgoods%20you%20are%20manufacturing.%20To%20strengthen%20the%20buying%20power%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20the%20cost-effectiveness%20of%20the%20resources%2C%20the%20first%20need%20is%20to%20create%20jobs.%20And%20I%20am%20purely%20talking%20from%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20standpoint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20standpoint%2C%20if%20we%20have%20a%20bigger%20coffer%2C%20we%20will%20be%20more%20interested%20in%20hiring%20resources%20who%20are%20specialised%20in%20the%20desired%20jobs.%20Cross-skilling%20is%20only%20a%20compromise%20on%20expertise.%20From%20a%20resource%20standpoint%2C%20since%20I%20have%20more%20time%2C%20I%20might%20like%20to%20learn%20new%20skills%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMoneycontrol%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fopinion%2Fdigital-india-act-heres-how-it-should-fix-indias-cybersecurity-weaknesses-11038701.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20India%20could%20fix%20its%20cybersecurity%20weakness.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20upcoming%20Digital%20India%20Act%20offers%20an%20opportunity%20to%20streamline%20and%20modernise%20India%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20framework%2C%20addressing%20the%20existing%20gaps%20and%20inefficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699253135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03144731%2Fimage-1469.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fstate-sponsored-cyber-attacks-against-india-went-up-by-278-between-2021-and-september-2023-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%202023%20India%20Threat%20Landscape%20Report%20by%20Singapore-based%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Cyfirma%2C%20India%20is%20the%20most%20targeted%20country%20globally%2C%20facing%2013.7%25%20of%20all%20cyber%20attacks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fstate-sponsored-cyber-attacks-against-india-went-up-by-278-between-2021-and-september-2023-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Prince%20William%20goes%20dragon%20boating%20in%20Singapore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699253103000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F146CE%2Fproduction%2F_131626638_p0gqy1pp.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67330598%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20was%20said%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Ckept%20up%20really%20well%E2%80%9D%20during%20a%20dragon%20boat%20training%20session.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A72%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%