C%20News%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Seema%20Sherghill%20arrived%20in%20Australia%20in%20April%202015%2C%20and%20spent%20about%20a%20year%20working%20at%20the%20high%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20official%20residence.%20She%20left%20the%20house%20in%20May%202016%20and%20was%20granted%20Australian%20citizenship%20in%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENeither%20the%20MEA%20or%20Suri%2C%20who%20had%20retired%20in%202019%2C%20took%20part%20in%20the%20court%20proceedings%20in%20Australia.%20There%20is%20no%20public%20statement%20from%20the%20Ministry%2C%20so%20far.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20single%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Elizabeth%20Draper%20observed%2C%20as%20per%20ABC%20News%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cemployment%20conditions%20bore%20no%20resemblance%20to%20what%20one%20would%20expect%20under%20Australian%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHer%20passport%20was%20taken%20from%20her%2C%20she%20worked%20seven%20days%20a%20week%2C%20was%20never%20permitted%20to%20take%20leave%20and%20was%20only%20allowed%20outside%20the%20house%20for%20brief%20periods%20a%20day%20when%20looking%20after%20Mr%20Suri%E2%80%99s%20dog.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Judge%20also%20ruled%20that%20the%20Indian%20diplomat%20was%20ineligible%20to%20claim%20foreign%20state%20immunity%2C%20because%20Shergill%20did%20not%20work%20for%20the%20High%20Commission%20itself%2C%20nor%20diplomatic%20immunity%2C%20as%20the%20engagement%20of%20a%20domestic%20worker%20was%20not%20an%20official%20function%20of%20his%20position.%20She%20ordered%20Suri%20to%20pay%20Sherghill%20more%20than%20A%24136%2C000%20plus%20interest%2C%20within%2060%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShergill%20had%20earlier%20worked%20with%20Suri%20when%20he%20had%20been%20the%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20Australia.%20She%20had%20travelled%20to%20Australia%20on%20an%20official%20passport%20with%20a%20diplomatic%20visa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDevyani%20Khobragade%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20December%202013%2C%20an%20Indian%20diplomat%20Devyani%20Khobragade%20was%20strip-searched%20by%20US%20security%20officials%20on%20claims%20by%20her%20domestic%20help%20that%20she%20had%20not%20given%20her%20adequate%20compensation.%20It%20had%20led%20to%20relations%20between%20US%20and%20India%20nose-diving%20into%20a%20sudden%20crisis%2C%20before%20she%20finally%20flew%20back%20to%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20MEA%20subsequently%20modified%20the%20system%20of%20India-based%20domestic%20assistants%2C%20who%20were%20no%20longer%20considered%20%E2%80%98personal%20helps%E2%80%99%20but%20were%20employed%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20sources%2C%20Shergill%20refused%20to%20sign%20an%20undertaking%20in%20May%202016%20that%20was%20required%20from%20staff%20at%20all%20Indian%20diplomatic%20missions%20that%20they%20would%20return%20to%20India%20at%20the%20end%20of%20their%20three-year%20tenure.%20This%20was%20a%20new%20provision%20that%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20post-Khobragade%20affair.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20refusal%20to%20sign%20the%20undertaking%20meant%20cancellation%20of%20her%20contract%20and%20return%20to%20India%2C%20she%20was%20reportedly%20given%20several%20cautionary%20messages%20by%20the%20embassy%20officials.%20When%20she%20again%20refused%2C%20a%20ticket%20was%20bought%20by%20the%20High%20Commission%20for%20a%20flight%20to%20Delhi%20on%20May%2027%2C%202016.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20day%20before%20her%20flight%2C%20she%20left%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20official%20residence%2C%20following%20which%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20filed%20a%20%E2%80%98missing%20person%E2%80%99%20complaint%20with%20the%20Australian%20Federal%20Police%2C%20as%20per%20informed%20sources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EABC%20News%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20quoted%20Shergill%20as%20stating%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Cresponsible%20for%20doing%20everything%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20residence%2C%20known%20as%20India%20House.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20were%20away%2C%20instead%20of%20my%20usual%20chores%2C%20Mr%20Suri%20or%20his%20wife%20usually%20would%20ask%20me%20to%20make%20large%20batches%20of%20samosas%20and%20freeze%20them%2C%20or%20to%20clean%20the%20silverware%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20claimed%20to%20have%20worked%20seven%20days%20a%20week%20for%2017.5%20hours%20per%20day%2C%20with%20her%20official%20duties%20being%20cleaning%20the%20house%2C%20preparing%20meals%20and%20tidying%20the%20garden.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Shergill%20claimed%20that%20she%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20leave%20the%20house%20except%20to%20walk%20the%20dog%2C%20Indian%20sources%20claimed%20that%20she%20had%20remote%20access%20to%20the%20main%20gate%20to%20allow%20entry%20and%20exit%20of%20visitors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20court%20judgment%20was%20based%20on%20the%20premise%20that%20Seema%20Shergill%20was%20employed%20in%20a%20private%20capacity%20in%20non-diplomatic%20household%2C%20which%20was%20inaccurate.%20They%20pointed%20out%20that%20she%20travelled%20on%20an%20official%20passport%20and%20that%20the%20Australian%20government%20had%20given%20her%20a%20diplomatic%20visa%20and%20identity%20card%20to%20show%20that%20she%20was%20in%20service%20at%20the%20High%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20sources%20claimed%20that%20India-based%20diplomats%20and%20staff%20are%20paid%20salaries%20as%20per%20Indian%20scales%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20this%20judgement%20was%20seemingly%20in%20viol